properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Long-lasting blizzard conditions with potentially damaging winds and persistent visibility near zero in blowing snow are expected or occurring. A strong ridge of high pressure is in place over the Northwest Territories. With low pressure over Alaska, strong winds with blowing snow are expected for northern sections of the Dempster. Winds have diminished this afternoon but will pick up near midnight as the gradient increases again. Near the Richardson Mountains, winds will reach 80 km/h gusting to 100 at times resulting in blizzard conditions. Blizzard conditions are forecast to improve by late Thursday. ### Travel is expected to be extremely hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather in British Columbia or Yukon, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm or #YTStorm.
